                <head>293. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Conference on Antarctica met at Washington, October 15–December 1, with
                    representatives of Argentina, Australia, Belgium, Chile, France, Japan, New
                    Zealand, Norway, the Soviet Union, the Union of South Africa, the United
                    Kingdom, and the United States in attendance. Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_PH5">Herman Phleger</persName>, head of the U.S. Delegation, was
                    elected chairman of the conference. The first plenary session was held October
                    15 from 11 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. and from 3 to 4:30 p.m. in the auditorium of the
                    Department of the Interior. For texts of the opening statements made by each
                    delegation, see <hi rend="italic">The Conference on Antarctica, Washington,
                        October 15–December 1, 1959</hi> (Washington, September 1960), pages
                    2–30.</p>
            </div>
